.TH "drbd_bitmap_io" 9 "drbd_bitmap_io" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drbd_bitmap_io \- Does an IO operation on the whole bitmap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drbd_bitmap_io
.BI "(struct drbd_device *device "  ","
.BI "int (*io_fn)(struct drbd_device *) "  ","
.BI "char *why "  ","
.BI "enum bm_flag flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
DRBD device.
.IP "io_fn" 12
IO callback to be called when bitmap IO is possible
.IP "why" 12
Descriptive text of the reason for doing the IO
.IP "flags" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
freezes application IO while that the actual IO operations runs. This
functions MAY NOT be called from worker context.
